  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling 25,000 dollars from their employer. However, I must take into account several mitigating factors, including the defendant's lack of any prior criminal record and the fact that partial restitution has already been made. The spectator's outburst of a 10-year demand is emotionally driven and legally irrelevant to these proceedings. Balancing the severity of the financial crime with the defendant's background and efforts to make amends, a moderate period of incarceration is warranted to serve as both punishment and deterrence without being unduly harsh. Therefore, a sentence of 12 months of incarceration is appropriate.",
